\f0\fs28 \cf0 When working on a long piece of writing, you may want to refer to research or other parts of the manuscript. In Scrivener, you can split the main editor into two and have different documents (or the same document) open in each.\
Let\'92s try that now by going to 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::0>
\f2\b View > Editor Layout > Split Horizontally
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::0>
\f0\fs28 .\
Alternatively, click on the button in the right of the editor header view (the square with the horizontal line through its middle):\
