\cf0 This document is now displayed in two panes.\
Note:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Through the 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::0>
\f2\b View > Editor Layout
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::0>
\f0\fs28  menu, you can switch to a vertical (side-by-side) split or remove the split to return to a single editor.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Option-clicking on the split button in the header view toggles between horizontal and vertical split mode. (Make sure the editor is split horizontally for this tutorial - the button splits vertically by default.)\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Clicking on the split button in the header view when there is a split removes the split, returning to single editor mode.\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Now let\'92s load a 
\f3\i different
\f0\i0  document in one of the editors:\
\pard\tx560\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f4\i\b \cf0 Select any document in the binder, and it will be shown in the editor that currently has the focus.
\f0\i0\b0  (You can tell which editor currently has the focus because when there is a split, the header bar of the focussed editor takes on the system accent colour.)\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 You can also drag a document from the binder to the header view of the editor in which you wish to view it. Let\'92s do that now:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Make sure that this document, \'93Splitting the Editor\'94, is visible in the bottom pane.\
{\listtext	2.	}Drag \'93Sunset\'94 from inside the \'93Research\'94 folder onto the header view of the top pane.\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 You can use the split view to view any two documents in Scrivener alongside one another, allowing you to refer to a text, PDF, image or media document in one editor while typing in another.\
Try loading different documents into the other editor now. Remember, you can do this in two ways:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Drag a document from the binder to the header view of the other editor.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Click into the editor you want to use so that its header changes colour, and then select a document in the binder.\

